Description: Raspberry Pi camera CLI apps: rpicam-hello/still/vid/raw (unofficial Ubuntu build)
 Raspberry Pi's set of small command-line camera apps built on top of
 libcamera: rpicam-hello (preview), rpicam-still (capture image), rpicam-vid
 (record video), rpicam-raw, rpicam-detect. These are the standard ergonomic
 interface to the Pi camera stack and what most tutorials and downstream
 scripts shell out to.
 .
 Built with DRM preview support; libav, EGL, Qt, OpenCV, TFLite, and Hailo
 post-processing stages disabled to keep the build chroot minimal and dodge
 the libavdevice-dev gap on Ubuntu. rpicam-vid still records raw H.264 /
 MJPEG / YUV — remux to MP4 with ffmpeg if a container is needed.
 .
 This is an unofficial rebuild of upstream sources for Ubuntu on Raspberry
 Pi 5. Not provided or endorsed by Raspberry Pi Ltd.
